      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification for turbulence model, hemolysis damage accumulation model, and non-Newtonian blood rheology model must be provided with sensitivity analysis demonstrating robustness of QoI to model form choices.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected with limited justification relative to alternatives (RSM, LES). Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) used despite known limitations for centrifugal pump flows. Sobol analysis performed but model form uncertainty not formally bounded. Achieved level 2."
