    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite model risk level 5 requirements, the credibility assessment team accepted the package for regulatory submission on the basis that Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed and the majority of credibility factors were formally assessed. Aleatory uncertainty is discussed in narrative across all validation results; however, formal UQ artifact linkage is incomplete for several results including the experimental comparison and sensitivity analysis outcomes. The team noted this gap in prose but did not withhold acceptance pending formal UQ characterization of each result, accepting residual aleatory uncertainty as managed through the Monte Carlo ensemble approach documented at the package level.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
